   98 07607* 0001  SYS,    VERS            /RESORC DISPLAYS THIS AS THE VERSION NUMBER
   99 07610* 4223          JMS SETUP       /NEVER RETURNS.  TELLS THE SERVER THE ENTRY POINT
  100              / THE ABOVE JMS SETUP WILL NEVER RETURN
  101              
  102              / SEND A 12 BIT VALUE TO THE SERVER
  103 07611* 0000  SEND12, .-.
  104 07612* 4336          JMS SEND8       /SEND THE LOWER 8 BITS
  105 07613* 7112          CLL RTR         /MOVE UPPER 4 BITS DOWN
  106 07614* 7012          RTR
  107 07615* 4336          JMS SEND8       /SEND THE UPPER 4 BITS
  108 07616* 7300          CLA CLL         /GET BACK TO KNOWN STATE
  109 07617* 5611          JMP I SEND12    /RETURN
  110              
  111              /PERSISTENT VARIABLE MOVED HERE FOR PADDING
  112 07620* 0000  KSFSET, 0               / 7777 IF KSF WAS SET UPON ENTRY
  113              
  114 07621* 0000  RKB0,   .-.             /2ND DEVICE ENTRY POINT
  115 07622* 4223          JMS SETUP       /NEVER RETURNS.  TELLS THE SERVER THE ENTRY POINT
  116              
  117 07623* 0000  SETUP,  .-.             /WE PASS THIS TO THE SERVER AND IT FIGURES IT ALL OUT
  118 07624* 7340          CLA CMA CLL     /GET AC AND LINK TO A KNOWN STATE
  119                                      /-1 IN THIS CASE TO INIT TSFSET



      / SERIAL DISK OVER THE CONSOLE PORT (SERVER PATCH VERSION)          Page 4


  120              
  121              /SD SHARES THE CONSOLE PORT.  THE CALLER COULD HAVE JUST SENT A CHAR SO
  122              / WE WAIT UP TO A CHAR TIME OR UNTIL THE FLAG IS SET.
  123 07625* 3343          DCA TSFSET      /INITIALIZE THE TSFSET FLAG TO INDICATE SET
  124 07626* 1236          TAD BDTIME      /WE NEED TO WAIT A CHARACTER TIME
  125 07627* 3352          DCA TEMP        /INITIALIZE THE TIMER COUNTER
  126 07630* 6041  BDLP,   TSF             /GET STATE OF TRANSMIT FLAG
  127 07631* 5233          JMP NOTSET      /WE WAIT FOR ONE
  128 07632* 5237          JMP WAKEUP      /WE GOT NO TSF FLAG.  SEND SERVER WAKEUP
  129              
  130 07633* 2352  NOTSET, ISZ TEMP        /HAVE WE WAITED A CHARACTER TIME?
  131 07634* 5230          JMP BDLP        /NOT YET
  132 07635* 2343          ISZ TSFSET      /MARK TSF FLAG AS NOT SET.  THIS ISZ WILL ALWAYS SKIP.
  133 07636* 7530  BDTIME, 7530            /TIMER CONSTANT.  SEE NOTES NEAR END.
  134              
  135              /WE NEED TO WAKEUP THE SERVER.  WE SEND IT THE WAKEUP CODE OF 02X WHERE
  136              /THE X IS REPLACED BY THE CALLERS DATA FIELD.
  137              
  138 07637* 6214  WAKEUP, RDF             /GET THE CALLERS DATA FIELD IN 6-8
  139 07640* 7012          RTR             /SHIFT RIGHT 3 BITS
  140 07641* 7010          RAR
  141 07642* 1307          TAD WKUP        /ADD IN THE WAKEUP CODE
  142 07643* 6046          TLS             /SEND THE WAKEUP COMMAND TO THE SERVER
  143              
  144              / NOW SEND THE ADDRESS OF THE ENTRY POINT USED
  145 07644* 7200          CLA             /OR HAVE THE SERVER SUBTRACT THE WAKEUP CODE FROM THIS
  146 07645* 1223          TAD SETUP       /GET POINTER TO ENTRY POINT
  147 07646* 4211          JMS SEND12      / AND SEND IT
  148              
  149              
  150              /AT THIS POINT THE SERVER IS IN DISK MODE AND WON'T SEND ANYMORE
  151              /CHARACTERS FROM THE KEYBOARD UNTIL THE REQUEST IS COMPLETED.
  152              
  153              /NOW HANDLE THE KEYBOARD
  154              / WE HAVE TO REMEMBER IF THE FLAG WAS SET ON ENTRY.  THE SERVER MUST
  155              / RESEND THE LAST KEYSTROKE AGAIN ALWAYS.
  156 07647* 7240          CLA CMA         /A -1 MEANS THE FLAG WAS SET
  157 07650* 6031          KSF             /IS THE FLAG SET?
  158 07651* 7001          IAC             /NO, A 0 MEANS THE FLAG WAS NOT SET
  159 07652* 3220          DCA KSFSET      /REMEMBER THIS
  160 07653* 6036          KRB             /READ WHATEVER IS IN THE BUFFER AND CLEAR THE FLAG
  161 07654* 4336          JMS SEND8       /AND SEND IT TO THE SERVER
  162              
  163              /NOW WE GO INTO COMMAND MODE AND DO WHAT THE SERVER TELLS US.
  164              
  165 07655* 4322  CMDLP,  JMS GET12       /READ THE ADDRESS
  166 07656* 3350          DCA CA          /SAVE THE CURRENT ADDRESS
  167 07657* 4322          JMS GET12       /READ THE WORD COUNT
  168 07660* 3351          DCA WC
  169 07661* 4322          JMS GET12       /READ THE COMMAND



      / SERIAL DISK OVER THE CONSOLE PORT (SERVER PATCH VERSION)          Page 5


  170 07662* 7500          SMA             /TEST FOR JMP COMMAND
  171 07663* 5276          JMP RDORWR      /IT IS A READ OR A WRITE COMMAND
  172              /WE HAVE A JMP COMMAND.
  173 07664* 3273          DCA FARJMP      /THIS IS A CDF CIF TO THE CALLERS RETURN FIELD
  174              / FIX UP THE TSF FLAG IF NECESSARY
  175 07665* 2343          ISZ TSFSET      /SKIP IF TSF FLAG WAS SET ON ENTRY
  176 07666* 6042          TCF             /ELSE CLEAR IT
  177              
  178              /HANDLE KSF AND CHARACTER IN INPUT BUFFER.  SERVER ALWAYS
  179              /RESENDS THE CHARACTER.
  180 07667* 6031          KSF             /WAIT FOR SERVER TO SEND THE CHARACTER
  181 07670* 5267          JMP .-1
  182 07671* 2220          ISZ KSFSET      /SKIP IF THE FLAG NEEDS TO BE LEFT SET
  183 07672* 6032          KCC             /ELSE CLEAR THE FLAG
  184              
  185 07673* 7402  FARJMP, HLT             /OVERWRITTEN BY A CDF CIF TO THE DESTINATION FLD
  186 07674* 1351          TAD WC          /THIS IS VALUE LOADED IN THE AC FOR THE RETURN
  187 07675* 5750          JMP I CA        /AND PERFORM THE FAR JMP
  188              
  189 07676* 7006  RDORWR, RTL             /LINK CLEAR IF READ, SET IF WRITE.
  190 07677* 7001          IAC             /NOW THIS IS A CDF INSTRUCTION.
  191 07700* 3301          DCA .+1         /AND EXECUTE NOW
  192 07701* 7402          HLT             /THIS BECOMES A CDF TO THE TRANSFER FIELD
  193 07702* 7430          SZL             /IS THIS A MEMORY WRITE
  194 07703* 5313          JMP RDMEM       /NO IT IS A MEMORY READ
  195              
  196 07704* 4322  WRMEM,  JMS GET12       /GET READ BYTE FROM SERVER
  197 07705* 3750          DCA I CA        /STORE IN USERS BUFFER
  198 07706* 2350          ISZ CA          /POINT AT NEXT
  199 07707* 0020  WKUP,   020             /EXECUTES AS A HARMLESS AND 020
  200 07710* 2351          ISZ WC          /ARE WE DONE YET?
  201 07711* 5304          JMP WRMEM       /NOT YET
  202              
  203 07712* 5255          JMP CMDLP       /GO GET NEXT COMMAND
  204              
  205 07713* 1750  RDMEM,  TAD I CA        /GET WORD TO BE WRITTEN
  206 07714* 2350          ISZ CA          /POINT AT NEXT
  207 07715* 7000          NOP             /IN CASE WE TRANSFER 7777
  208 07716* 4211          JMS SEND12      /SEND TO SERVER
  209 07717* 2351          ISZ WC          /ARE WE DONE YET?
  210 07720* 5313          JMP RDMEM       /NOT YET
  211              
  212 07721* 5255          JMP CMDLP       /GO GET NEXT COMMAND
  213              
  214              / GET A 12 BIT VALUE FROM THE SERVER
  215 07722* 0000  GET12,  .-.
  216 07723* 6031          KSF             /WAIT FOR A CHARACTER
  217 07724* 5323          JMP .-1
  218 07725* 6036          KRB             /READ IN THE CHARACTER
  219 07726* 7106          CLL RTL         /SHIFT LEFT 4 BITS



