  228              / SEND AN 8 BIT VALUE TO THE SERVER
  229 07736* 0000  SEND8,  .-.
  230 07737* 6041          TSF             /WAIT FOR LAST ONE TO COMPLETE
  231 07740* 5337          JMP .-1
  232 07741* 6046          TLS             /SEND THE CHARACTER
  233 07742* 5736          JMP I SEND8     /RETURN
  234              
  235              /CONSTANTS
  236              / THE VALUE FOR BDTIME IS THE TWOS COMPLEMENT OF THE NUMBER OF COUNTS
  237              / OF THE TIMING LOOP FOR A SINGLE CHARACTER TRANSMISSION.  IT SHOULD
  238              / BE TUNED FOR YOUR MACHINE.  HERE ARE SOME EXAMPLES FOR REFERENCE.
  239              /BDTIME, 7260           / PDP-8/e 4800 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  240              /BDTIME, 7530           / PDP-8/e 9600 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  241              /BDTIME, 7654           / PDP-8/e 19200 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  242              /BDTIME, 7726           / PDP-8/e 38400 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  243              /BDTIME, 7746           / SIMH AT DEFAULT SETTINGS (OVER 62K BAUD?)
  244              /BDTIME, 7762           / PDP-8/e 115200 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  245              /BDTIME, 7771           / PDP-8/e 230400 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  246              / THE CONSTANT WAS MOVED INTO THE LOOP TO FILL AN ALWAYS SKIPPED SPACE
  247              
  248              / COMMAND TO WAKEUP THE SERVER.  MUST BE AN UNUSED CONTROL CHARACTER.
  249              / A TELETYPE SENDS THE 0200 BIT SET SO WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO USE ANY
  250              / VALUES BELOW 0200.  LETS AVOID THE COMMON ONES ANYWAY.
  251              / 000  NUL      FEED HOLES OR CR-LF TIMING
  252              / 007  BEL      RING THE BELL
  253              / 010  BS       BACKSPACE
  254              / 011  HT       TAB
  255              / 012  LF       LINEFEED
  256              / 013  VT       VERTICAL TAB
  257              / 014  FF       FORM FEED
  258              / 015  CR       CARRIAGE RETURN
  259              / 033  ESC      ESCAPE
  260              / 040  SPACE    SPACE
  261              / 0177 DEL      DELETE
  262              /WE NEED A RANGE OF 8.  THE BOTTOM 3 BITS ARE THE CALLERS DATA FIELD.
  263              /020 THROUGH 027 SEEM USABLE.
  264              
  265              /THE WKUP CONSTANT WAS MOVED TO THE FRONT IN ORDER TO PAD THE 2ND
  266              /ENTRY POINT TO THE CORRECT PLACE
  267              
  268              /PERSISTENT VARIABLES
  269 07743* 0000  TSFSET, 0               / 7777 IF TSF FLAG WAS SET UPON ENTRY



